Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and conversational analysis using neural models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to enrich existing datasets using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses recurrent neural models for annotation. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possibility as one of the datasets used in the paper (IEMOCAP) contains audio recordings. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper aims to improve the performance of natural dialogue systems.
